@* _ViewStart.cshtml sets a default layout for all views in a folder, 
so you don’t have to repeat it in each view) *@
@{
    Layout = "_Layout";
}

@* What happens behind the scenes

When you return a view:

return View();

ASP.NET does this:

1. Find the view (e.g. Index.cshtml)
2. Run _ViewStart.cshtml
3. Apply Layout setting
4. Render the view inside the layout *@